    "By doing so, the model can emphasize the most informative parts of the input and ignore irrelevant or less important elements, leading to improved performance in various sequence modeling tasks.Where: Q, K and V represent the query, key and value matrices.",
    "They are obtained by linear projections of the input sequence X using the weight matrices W Q, W K, and W V. The symbol d k denotes the dimension of the key and query vectors.",
    "This is typically set to the square root ofAttention(Q, K, V) = softmax QK T d k Vthe dimension of the input embeddings or hidden states, in order to stabilize the attention scores.According to the above equations, the vector QK T provides important information to the vector V.Attention mechanisms are a highly researched topic for several reasons.",
    "Foremost, any model with an attention mechanism outperforms baseline techniques.",
    "Additionally, attention models can be trained using basic recurrent neural networks through back-propagation."
